ero.aero |date=20 November 2011 |accessdate=20 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nFrom February 2017, Russia is changing to use QNH and Feet below the Transition Level. The first airport to use this is ULLI/St. Petersburg.<ref>http://flightservicebureau.org/big-change-russia-finally-moving-to-qnh/</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[International Civil Aviation Organization#Use of the International System of Units|ICAO recommendations on use of the International System of Units]]\n*[[Flight planning]]\n*[[Gillham code]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}<!--added above categories/infobox footers by script-assisted edit-->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Flight Level}}\n[[Category:Altitudes in aviation]]\n[[Category:Air traffic control]]\n", "name_user": "GnatFriend", "label": "safe", "comment": "correct punctuation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flight_level"}
{"title_page": "Eli Davies", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox rugby league biography\n|name                = Eli Davies\n|fullname            = Eli Davies\n|nickname            = \n|image               = \n|imagesize           = \n|caption             = \n|birth_place         = Wales\n|birth_date          = \n|death_date          =\n|death_place         = unknown\n|height              = \n|weight              = \n|position            = {{rlp|SO}}\n|club1               = [[Wigan Warriors|Wigan]]\n|year1start          = 1903\n|year1end            = 04\n|appearances1        = 26\n|tries1              = 2\n|goals1              = 8\n|fieldgoals1         = \n|points1             = 22\n|teamA               = [[Other Nationalities rugby league team|Other Nationalities]]\n|yearAstart          = 1904\n|yearAend            =\n|appearancesA        = 1\n|triesA              = \n|goalsA              = \n|fieldgoalsA         = \n|pointsA             = \n|new                 = yes\n|retired             = yes\n|updated             = 10 July 2010\n|source              = <ref name=\"Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/e-davies--w-/summary.html|title=Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org|website=rugbyleagueproject.org|date=31 December 2017|accessdate=1 January 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Eli Davies''' (birth unknown \u2013 death unknown) was a Welsh professional [[rugby league]] footballer who played in the 1900s. He played at representative level for [[Other Nationalities rugby league team|Other Nationalities]], and at club level for [[Wigan Warriors|Wigan]], as a {{rlp|so}}, i.e. number 6.<ref name=\"Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org\"/><ref>{{cite book| first1= Graham| last1= Williams| first2= Peter| last2= Lush| first3= David| last3= Farrar| title= The British Rugby League Records Book| publisher= London League| isbn= 978-1-903659-49-6| year= 2009| pages= 108\u2013114}}</ref>\n\n==International honours==\nEli Davies won a [[Cap (sport)|cap]] playing {{rlp|so}} for [[Other Nationalities rugby league team|Other Nationalities]] in the 9-3 victory over England at [[Central Park (Wigan)|Central Park, Wigan]] on Tuesday 5 April 1904, in the first ever international rugby league match.<ref name=\"The First International Rugby League Match\">{{cite web|first=Sean|last=Fagan|url=http://www.rl1895.com/1904.htm|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120204062114/http://www.rl1895.com/1904.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=4 February 2012|title=The First International Rugby League Match|publisher=rl1895.com|accessdate=14 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://wigan.rlfans.com/readarticle.php?article_id=314 Statistics at wigan.rlfans.com]\n*[http://www.wigantoday.net/news/memento_of_a_great_dai_in_wigan_1_198189 Memento of a Great Dai in Wigan]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Davies, Eli}}\n[[Category:Other Nationalities rugby league team players]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Place of death missing]]\n[[Category:Rugby league five-eighths]]\n[[Category:Welsh rugby league players]]\n[[Category:Wigan Warriors players]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox rugby league biography\n|name                = Eli Davies\n|fullname            = Eli Davies\n|nickname            = \n|image               = \n|imagesize           = \n|caption             = \n|birth_place         = Wales\n|birth_date          = \n|death_date          =\n|death_place         = unknown\n|height              = \n|weight              = \n|position            = {{rlp|SO}}\n|club1               = [[Wigan Warriors|Wigan]]\n|year1start          = 1903\n|year1end            = 04\n|appearances1        = 26\n|tries1              = 2\n|goals1              = 8\n|fieldgoals1         = \n|points1             = 22\n|teamA               = [[Other Nationalities rugby league team|Other Nationalities]]\n|yearAstart          = 1904\n|yearAend            =\n|appearancesA        = 1\n|triesA              = \n|goalsA              = \n|fieldgoalsA         = \n|pointsA             = \n|new                 = yes\n|retired             = yes\n|updated             = 10 July 2010\n|source              = <ref name=\"Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/e-davies--w-/summary.html|title=Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org|publisher=rugbyleagueproject.org|date=31 December 2017|accessdate=1 January 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Eli Davies''' (birth unknown \u2013 death unknown) was a Welsh professional [[rugby league]] footballer who played in the 1900s. He played at representative level for [[Other Nationalities rugby league team|Other Nationalities]], and at club level for [[Wigan Warriors|Wigan]], as a {{rlp|so}}, i.e. number 6.<ref name=\"Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org\"/><ref>{{cite book| first1= Graham| last1= Williams| first2= Peter| last2= Lush| first3= David| last3= Farrar| title= The British Rugby League Records Book| publisher= London League| isbn= 978-1-903659-49-6| year= 2009| pages= 108\u2013114}}</ref>\n\n==International honours==\nEli Davies won a [[Cap (sport)|cap]] playing {{rlp|so}} for [[Other Nationalities rugby league team|Other Nationalities]] in the 9-3 victory over England at [[Central Park (Wigan)|Central Park, Wigan]] on Tuesday 5 April 1904, in the first ever international rugby league match.<ref name=\"The First International Rugby League Match\">{{cite web|first=Sean|last=Fagan|url=http://www.rl1895.com/1904.htm|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120204062114/http://www.rl1895.com/1904.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=4 February 2012|title=The First International Rugby League Match|publisher=rl1895.com|accessdate=14 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*