aterinburg]], Russia\n|\n|-\n| {{no2}}Loss\n| align=center| 14\u201310\u20133\n| Mikhail Avetisyan\n| Submission (strikes)\n| IAFC \u2013 Absolute Fighting Championship 2000 (Day 2)\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2000|April|29}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 2:53\n| [[Moscow]], Russia \n| <small>IAFC - Absolute Fighting [[Pankration]] Championship 2000 (Quarter-finals).</small>\n|-\n| {{no2}}Loss\n| align=center| 14\u20139\u20133\n| [[Renato Sobral]]\n| Decision (unanimous)\n| rowspan=2| [[King of Kings Tournament 1999|RINGS: King of Kings 1999 Block A]]\n| rowspan=2|{{dts|format=dmy|1999|October|28}}\n| align=center| 2\n| align=center| 5:00\n| rowspan=2|[[Tokyo]], Japan\n| <small>RINGS: King of Kings Tournament 1999 (Round of 16).</small>\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 14\u20138\u20133\n| [[Achmed Labasanov]]\n| TKO (kick)\n| align=center| 2\n| align=center| 3:33\n| <small>RINGS: King of Kings Tournament 1999 (Round of 32).</small>\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 13\u20138\u20133\n| [[Dave van der Veen]]\n| Submission (armbar)\n| T.F.F - Total Fight KRG 5\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1999|October|3}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 1:47\n| [[Milton Keynes]], England\n| <small>Retained U.T.F Super-Fight Heavyweight Shootfighting title.</small> \n|-\n| {{draw}}Draw\n| align=center| 12\u20138\u20133\n| [[Satoshi Honma]]\n| Draw\n| RINGS: Battle Genesis Vol. 5\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1999|September|15}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 20:00\n| [[Tokyo]], Japan\n|<ref>[http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/shoot/rings/rings1999.html#091599]. Retrieved 28 September 2011.</ref>\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 12\u20138\u20132\n| [[Ricardo Fyeet]]\n| Submission ([[toe hold]])\n| [[1999 in Fighting Network Rings|RINGS: Rise 5th]]\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1999|August|19}}\n| align=center| 1\n| align=center| 15:01\n| [[Yokohama]], Japan\n|\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center| 11\u20138\u20132\n| [[Ryuki Ueyama]]\n| Disqualification ([[eye-gouging]])\n| [[1999 in Fighting Network Ri