|  ||  ||\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1992-10-25 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|NLD}} Jerrell Vjent || || [[Bromley]], [[England]] || || || || ||\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1992 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Everton Crawford || || [[Bedford]], [[England]] || Decision || 5 || 2:00 || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 | Retained BIKA British light-heavyweight Thai boxing title.\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1992-07-18 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Everton Crawford || B.I.K.A - Simply The Best || [[Bracknell]], [[England]] ||  ||  ||  || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 | Retained BIKA British light-heavyweight Thai boxing title.\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1992-07-03 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Bertil Queely || || [[Bedford]], [[England]] || KO (leg kicks) || 2 || || Kickboxing ||\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 | Won BIKA British light-heavyweight free-style title.\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1991-04-26 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Nik Pavlovic || || [[Bedford]], [[England]] || Decision || 5 || 2:00 || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 | Won BIKA British [[Kickboxing weight classes|light-heavyweight]] Thai boxing title.\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1991-03-09 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}}Tony Manterfield || An Evening of Kickboxing || [[Barnsley]], [[England]] || TKO (threw in the towel) || 7 || 3:00 || Kickboxing ||\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 | Won [[World Kickboxing Association|WKA]] British super-middleweight kickboxing title.\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#fbb;\"\n| 1990 || Loss ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Ian Ledson || || [[Wigan]], [[England]] || Decision || 5 || 2:00 || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 | For the WTBF British [[Kickboxing weight classes|Junior light-Heavyweight]] Thai boxing title.\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#fbb;\"\n| 1990 || Loss ||align=left|{{flagicon|WAL}} Eugene Valerio || || [[North Wales]], [[Wales]] || Decision || 5 || 2:00 || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 | For the IFCF [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Kickboxing weight classes|super-middleweight]] Thai boxing title.\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#fbb;\"\n| 1989 || Loss ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Richard Baxter || World Championship Kickboxing || [[England]] || Decision || 4 || 2:00 || Kickboxing ||\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1989 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Dave Gonquin || A Kickboxing Spectacular || [[Northampton]], [[England]] || KO (punches) || 3 || || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1989 || Win ||align=left| ||  || [[Nantwich]], [[England]] ||  Decision ||  ||  || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1989 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Graham Rookley ||  || [[Milton Keynes]], [[England]] || Decision || 4 || 2:00 || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1989-04-09 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Graham Chester || || [[Milton Keynes]], [[England]] || TKO || 2 ||  || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#cfc;\"\n| 1989-02-10 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Chris Haines ||  || [[Nantwich]], [[England]] ||  TKO || 2 ||  || Thai-Boxing ||\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#fbb;\"\n| 1989 || Loss ||align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} Brian Harris ||  || [[Winsford]], [[England]] || Decision || 3 || 2:00 || Kickboxing ||\n|}\n</div></div>\n'''''Legend''''': {{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win |border=1px solid #CCFFCC}}\n{{legend2|#FFBBBB|Loss |border=1px solid #FFBBBB}}\n{{legend2|#c5d2ea|Draw/No contest |border=1px solid #c5d2ea}}\n{{legend2|White|Notes |border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n|}\n\n==Submission grappling record==\n{{s-start